description:
HOW TO APPLY
Send your resume, contact information, and position title to careers@sienna-systems.com.
REQ#1901:Informatica Adminstrator - Alexandria, VA

This person will be part of the team that supports a growing Data Warehousing and Business Intelligence environment using Informatica, Oracle 11g/10g RDBMS, and SQL Server 2005/2008. This individual will be responsible for the following:
• Administering the Informatica environment on UNIX
• Apply patches / upgrades / hotfixes for Informatica PowerCenter
• Monitor performance, troubleshoot, and tune ETL processes
• Will be responsible for 24x7 support
• Work with Informatica vendor on any issues that arise
• Support the Informatica developer team as needed

1. Ensure development teams are following appropriate standards
2. Promote and deploy Informatica code
3. Assist development team at design time ensuring code will run at scale
4. Serve as an Informatica Developer as needed to get work completed.
• Write and maintain BASH shell scripts for administering the Informatica environment
• Design and implement appropriate error handling procedures
• Develop project, documentation, and ETL standards in conjunction with data architects
• Work with other team members to ensure standards around monitoring and management of the Informatica environment within the context of existing enterprise monitoring solutions

Qualifications:
• Excellent oral and written English communication skills

Specifically needs to be able to communicate well on phone calls
• Must be able to thrive under pressure and have a strong sense of ownership and responsibility for the project
• Minimum of 7-10 years of experience in the administration, architecture, design, and development of ETL programs using Informatica’s data integration tools;

1. Informatica experience must include working with large mission critical data systems (multiple terabytes in size with millions of rows processing per day)
2. Must be able to demonstrate mastery of Informatica command line utilities
3. Must be able to demonstrate mastery of quickly debugging and resolving issues that can arise with Informatica programs.
4. Must know how to navigate through the Informatica metadata repository
5. Expert knowledge of Informatica version 8.5 and above. Informatica version 9.x and above preferred;
6. Working with Informatica PowerExchange products is a plus
• Minimum 2 full lifecycle project experience with small development groups, e.g., leading ground up development of Informatica standards in one or more previous projects.
• Demonstrated ability to navigate through organizational and technical uncertainty
• Mastery of Unix concepts and commands, including process management, scripting, directory structures, file permissions and editors
• Solid background in Oracle database 11g

1. Must be able to read and understand an Oracle Explain Plan
2. Must understand and know Oracle hints
3. Solid experience building SQL queries, including creating sub-queries, minus/union, and inline queries
4. Stored procedure development experience
• Fluency with business concepts related to relational and dimensional data models
• BA/BS in computer science or equivalent experience
• Experience with large scale database application like Exadata would be a plus

description:
Job Title: Informatica IICS Developer
Contract
MClean, VA (Hybrid)

Description: The Informatica IICS Developer will be responsible for designing, developing, and implementing data integration solutions using Informatica Intelligent Cloud Services (IICS). This role requires expertise in ETL processes, data transformation, and integration workflows to ensure efficient data management and delivery.
Responsibilities:
Design and develop data integration workflows, mappings, and transformations using Informatica IICS.
Implement ETL processes to extract, transform, and load data from various sources into target systems.
Collaborate with business analysts and stakeholders to understand data requirements and translate them into technical solutions.
Optimize ETL processes for performance, scalability, and reliability.
Develop and maintain documentation for data integration processes and workflows.
Troubleshoot and resolve data integration issues and performance bottlenecks.
Perform data validation and quality checks to ensure data accuracy and integrity.
Stay up-to-date with Informatica IICS features, best practices, and emerging trends in data integration.
Work closely with the data engineering and analytics teams to support data-driven initiatives.
Required skills and qualifications:
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field.
Hands on experience in data integration and ETL development with Informatica IICS.Proficiency in designing and implementing data workflows, mappings, and transformations.
Strong understanding of relational databases, SQL, and data modeling concepts.

description:
Req ID: 328373

NTT DATA strives to hire exceptional, innovative and passionate individuals who want to grow with us. If you want to be part of an inclusive, adaptable, and forward-thinking organization, apply now.

We are currently seeking a Senior Informatica ETL Developer - REMOTE to join our team in Canton, Massachusetts (US-MA), United States (US).

Day to Day Responsibilities:
• Perform Data analysis, collect business requirements and identify business rules.
• Analyze, develop and support Data Integration, EDW and Data Management using Informatica, SQL, Oracle etc. platforms and tools.
• Collaborate with data modelling team to define data integration logic.
• Create data mappings necessary to fulfill the requirements.
• Build and test new ETL programs to fulfill the service requests.
• Automate the ETL processes and pipelines using scripting and Schedulers.
• Participate in Unit Testing, assist QA team in Integration Testing, and support Business team for UAT.
• Participate in code deployment and coordinate with different infrastructure teams during go-live, post-production, and continued support of end product.
• Debug data quality issues by analyzing the upstream sources and provide guidance to data integration team resolutions.
• Work closely work with DBAs to fix performance bottlenecks.

Minimum Requirements:
• Recent experience and clear responsibilities in an ETL / Extracts / Data Engineering lead developer capacity.
• 8 plus years of experience in data integration (ETL) with 6 or more in solution development using Informatica suite.
• 6 or more years of experience in RDBMS / Data Warehousing platforms on Oracle.
• Must be an expert in Linux shell scripting to introduce automation as part of solution delivery.
• Strong SQL knowledge and ability to write most complex queries.
• Conceptual understanding of logical and physical data modelling is a must, and a working experience is a plus.
• Ability to develop and maintain data integration/ETL specifications that states integration rules and mappings.
• Ability to use documentation tools such as MS Visio and MS PowerPoint to diagram integration data flows.
• Ability to communicate effectively with business and technical staff members.

Preferred Skills:
• Certifications in ETL and Data Warehouse platforms.
• Domain experience in Healthcare.
• Data profiling and implementation of automated solutions for data quality checks.

Education:
• Bachelor’s degree in Computer Engineering, Computer Science, Engineering, or related field of study

Where required by law, NTT DATA provides a reasonable range of compensation for specific roles. The starting pay range for this remote role is $105,840 - $245,000. This range reflects the minimum and maximum target compensation for the position across all US locations. Actual compensation will depend on a number of factors, including the candidate’s actual work location, relevant experience, technical skills, and other qualifications.

description:
Job Tittle: ETL Informatica Developer (IICS/ Snowflake must have)

Job Location: Dallas, TX

Duration: 12+ Months

10+ and W2 Only

Job Description:

Understands business objectives and problems, identifies alternative solutions, performs studies and cost/benefit analysis of alternatives. Analyzes user requirements, procedures, and problems to automate processing or to improve existing computer system: Confers with personnel of organizational units involved to analyze current operational procedures, identify problems, and learn specific input and output requirements, such as forms of data input, how data is to be; summarized, and formats for reports. Writes detailed description of user needs, program functions, and steps required to develop or modify computer program. Reviews computer system capabilities, specifications, and scheduling limitations to determine if requested program or program change is possible within existing system.

Additional job details and special considerations

We are seeking a highly experienced and motivated individual who specializes in Informatica Cloud Services (IICS). The ideal candidate will have deep technical expertise in multi-domain environments, enabling them to lead and deliver complex IICS implementations for our clients. This role requires a strong understanding of the Informatica toolset, including IICS and relevant business processes, along with excellent communication and client management skills.

CANDIDATE SKILLS AND QUALIFICATIONS

Extensive experience in designing, implementing, and managing Informatica IICS/snowflake solutions.

E2E implementation experience involving phases from design, realization, testing, to go-live

Deep understanding of Informatica data modeling, workflow, and integration capabilities and technologies, APIs, web services, and Informatica ETL tools.

Strong knowledge of data governance, data quality, and data integration principles.

Expertise in Azure Cloud and Snowflake Cloud Datawarehouse

Strong knowledge in SQL Queries and Query optimization

Ability to interact at a technical and non-technical level with Infrastructure, Network, Development, BA and QA

Development experience in high transaction/high availability systems.

Experience with analyzing and recommending solutions for Production issues short-term and long term.

Must have informatica PowerCenter/IICS development experience.

Knowledge and experience of managing reference data systems

Provide technical mentorship to junior ETL developers; establish coding standards, templates, and best practices.

Experience in Python with data science libraries

Experience in SQL programming and writing stored procedures, functions, views, SQL queries

Experience working with HIPAA regulations and handling protected health information (PHI) and personally identifiable information (PII).

Strong organizational and time management skills.

Data warehouse development experience

Experience with Snowflake

Experience in designing, optimizing, documenting, and implementing the operational aspects that support the Snowflake cloud data platform, including cost monitoring, optimizations, and user security auditing.

Experience in implementing and supporting automation for managing Snowflake accounts, databases, and access roles.

Experience and understanding in proposing and implementing database and Snowflake query performance optimizations.

Experience with Git hub integration with snowflake and load data.

description:
Informatica MDM Developer
Baltimore, MD
Work Style: Hybrid (3 days on-site; 2 days work from home)
Looking for local resources. Resources from MD, VA and DC area candidates are preferred and will be given weightage.
Duties:
• Informatica MDM Configuration: Configure and customize Informatica MDM to implement the Party Model, defining entity types, relationships, business rules, match and merge strategies, and user interfaces.
• Data Modeling: Work with data architects and stakeholders to design and maintain the data model for party-related entities within the MDM system, ensuring data accuracy and consistency.
• Data Integration: Integrate data from various source systems into Informatica MDM, performing data profiling, cleansing, and transformation to ensure data quality and integrity.
• Match and Merge: Implement match and merge rules to identify and consolidate duplicate records within the party entities, enabling a single and accurate view of each entity.
• Data Quality Management: Define and implement data quality rules and workflows within the MDM system to monitor, measure, and improve data quality across party [1] related data.
• Data Governance: Ensure adherence to data governance principles and data security best practices during MDM implementation and data management processes.
• Performance Optimization: Identify performance bottlenecks within the MDM system and optimize data loading, matching, and retrieval processes for efficient and seamless data operations.
• Collaboration: Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including data architects, data analysts, and business users, to understand data requirements and deliver MDM solutions that meet business needs.
• Testing and Validation: Conduct unit testing and integration testing to validate MDM configurations, ensuring accuracy and completeness of data within the MDM repository.
• Documentation: Maintain comprehensive technical documentation, including design specifications, configuration guides, and troubleshooting manuals for the MDM implementation.
Education Qualification:
• Bachelor's Degree from an accredited college or university with a major in Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering, Business, or other related scientific or technical discipline.
General Experience:
• At least six (6) years of experience in MDM Development experience with a focus on Informatica MDM and Party Model implementation.
• In-depth knowledge of Informatica MDM tools, including MDM Hub, Data Director, and ActiveVOS, and their functionalities for party entities.
• Familiarity with data modeling principles and data integration techniques.
• Strong understanding of data quality management and data governance practices within an MDM environment.
• Proficiency in data profiling, data cleansing, and data transformation processes.
• Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills to troubleshoot MDM-related issues.
• Strong communication and collaboration skills to work effectively with cross [1] functional teams and stakeholders.
• Prior experience with other MDM tools or cloud-based MDM solutions is advantageous.
• Informatica MDM certifications, such as Informatica MDM Developer Specialist or Informatica MDM Administrator Specialist, are highly desirable.

description:
Informatica Data Engineer

Works with client management to identify and specify business requirements and processes for diverse development platforms, computing environments e.g., host based, distributed systems, client server, software, hardware, technologies and tools. Formulates logical statements of business problems and devises, tests and implements efficient, cost effective application program solutions e.g., codes and or reuses existing code through the use of program development software alternatives and or integrates purchased solutions. Works independently, receives minimal guidance. Acts as a resource for colleagues with less experience. Solves complex problems takes a new perspective using existing solutions.

Responsibilities:
• Participate in team agile tasks and sessions such as story estimation, sprint planning demonstrations, and retrospectives.
• Establishes IDQ environments (Dev, Staging & Test) according to project requirements
• Design and develop data quality rules to evaluate and verify data transformations; update ETL scripts and data mappings to improve data migration activities using Informatica, Oracle, SQL, and other technologies.
• Evaluate legacy databases and ERD's to determine high confidence data quality and best transformation strategies to next generation data model
• Support data traceability, integrity and validation documentation along with ETL code, data dictionaries, profiles and script repository management.
• Work closely with Data Architects and Test Specialist to verify business rules and develop test plans and test scripts for data validation.
• Establish a portal for data analysts and customer to evaluate data anomalies /exceptions and data migration verifications.
• Develop reports to display validation and review progress; in addition to generating data cleansing and exception management reports.
• Work effectively with teammates; collaborate on shared work products and related tasks to ensure best solution derived.
• Expertise in Informatica (v.9/10) Data Quality (IDQ), Oracle RDBMS
• Bachelor’s Degree or an equivalent combination of education and training that provides the required knowledge, skills and abilities.
• Strong interpersonal skills

Qualifications/ Skills:

BS degree with 4+ years in SQL experience and 5+ years overall hands on Informatica Data Quality (IDQ) development experience.

Strong understanding on Data Profiling / Data Analyst tool.

Skilled and experienced in Informatica ETL tool suite including PowerCenter designer, workflow, monitoring and repository services.

Proficient with Informatica ETL Integration using Teradata, Oracle, Mainframe, and SQL Server databases.

Understanding of reusability, parameterization, and workflow design concepts.

Performs technical walk-through as needed to communicate design/coded solution and to seek input from team members.

Strong Programing and SQL skills

Informatica Admin experience is a plus.

Excellent oral and written communication and interpersonal skills.

Strong organizational, multi-tasking, and time-management skills preferred.

Ability to work independently or within a team for problem resolution.

Strong knowledge of Microsoft Office tool set.

Company Description

Halo Group is a premier provider of IT talent. We place technology experts within
the teams of the world’s leading companies to help them build innovative
businesses that keep them one step closer to their customers and one step
ahead of the competition. We offer a meaningful work environment for
employees, attractive and interesting engagements for consultants, and cutting-edge
digital innovation for our customers.

We delight in helping our customers execute their digital vision. Big projects or
small, Halo Group knows that by combining the highest quality talent with our
unwavering support, we will become an invaluable extension of the team. Halo
Group's experienced consultants in Detroit, Atlanta and Dallas specialize in all
areas of product/project governance, UX/UI, multi-platform applications, quality
assurance/testing, cloud computing, and data analytics.

Since its inception, Halo Group has been recognized for numerous awards, including:
• INC 5000
• Future 50
• 101 Best and Brightest
• Michigan 50 Companies to Watch

- Goldline Research - “Most Dependable Companies”
- Ernst & Young - “Entrepreneur of the Year” Finalist

Job Description
• Designs, develops, modifies, configures, debugs Informatica workflows using Informatica PowerCenter and PowerExchange CDC tools
• Design technical and Business solutions in our change data capture technologies.
• Build infrastructure to extract and format captured change data and provide that data to other Informatica components and products.
• Expertise in handling data recovery, solution designing, Production implementation, Testing and support of interfaces PWC and PWX.
• Responsible for the development/customization of interfaces, conversions, and enhancements
• Analyses existing applications and systems and formulates logic for new systems, devises logic procedures, logical database design, performs coding and tests/debugs programs
• Performs technical walk-through as needed to communicate design/coded solution and to seek input from team members
• Implements data clean-up procedures, data import/export utilities, transformations, scripts, stored procedures, and execution of test plans for loading the data successfully into the targets
• Performs Data analysis, data mapping, data loading
• Responsible for the development and documentation of deliverables, and specifications on a project-by-project basis as defined in the IT Methodology, in collaboration with business analyst and other project team members
• Performs migration of workflows from development/Test to production environment and provide post-deployment support
• Documents all technical specifications and associate project deliverables
• Should have worked in multi-location delivery environment
• Preferred worked with multiple databases like Netezza,Oracle etc.

• Bachelor's Degree in computer science/related field or equivalent experience
• Professional Informatica certification a PLUS

• 3+ years of experience in development, maintenance, and enhancement of Informatica Mappings, Work-flows, and processes
• 4+ yrs. experience in Power Exchange CDC tools and should have worked extracting data from different source system like SAP, Oracle, and AS400 etc.
• Good Knowledge on DWH concepts
• Experience in developing and deploying Informatica in Unix and Oracle 11g database environment
• Experience in performance trouble shooting and remediation

Additional Information
• * U.S. Citizens and those who are authorized to work independently in the United States are encouraged to apply. We are unable to sponsor at this time.
This is a Full-Time / Permanent job opportunity.
Only US Citizen, Green Card Holder, GC-EAD, H4-EAD & L2-EAD can apply.
• * All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.

description:
Description

At CSpring, we believe infrastructure and insight go hand in hand. We’re looking for a seasoned Informatica ETL Developer to join our Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) team in support of a major healthcare data transformation initiative. This role is instrumental in building and maintaining robust data integration pipelines that ensure timely, trusted insights across Medicaid systems.

Whether you’re optimizing job schedules, scripting solutions in Teradata, or leading performance tuning efforts, you’ll be working on meaningful projects that power decision-making and improve healthcare delivery for real people.

Why You’ll Love Working Here
• Build What Matters – Play a key role in evolving data infrastructure that improves health outcomes across state Medicaid programs.
• People-First Culture – We prioritize your growth, your wellbeing, and your voice—because consulting is personal.
• Technical Autonomy – Own your craft while collaborating with a cross-functional team of analysts, architects, and policy experts.
• Innovation with Integrity – Solve complex problems while mentoring others and continuously improving system performance.
What You’ll Do
• Design, develop, and optimize ETL solutions using Informatica PowerCenter.
• Implement automated data staging, integration, and scheduling processes across large datasets.
• Build, test, and maintain mappings, mapplets, workflows, and sessions using advanced Informatica transformations.
• Administer ETL environments (development and production), including backups, recovery, and system tuning.
• Write and optimize complex SQL and Unix Shell scripts to support Teradata-based data marts and reporting layers.
• Participate in solution design, requirements analysis, testing, and documentation activities.
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams and clients to align solutions with business needs and timelines.
• Provide technical guidance and mentorship to junior developers and analysts.
• Keep up with new technologies and recommend improvements to enhance performance and scalability.

Requirements
• 7+ years of experience in ETL development with Informatica PowerCenter
• 5+ years of experience with Teradata (v17+) and tools such as Fastload, TPT, Multiload
• 5+ years of experience in ETL environment administration (PowerCenter)
• 5+ years of writing and tuning complex SQL queries
• 2+ years of Unix Shell scripting (Bash/Korn)
• Strong communication, documentation, and mentoring abilities
• Bachelor’s or advanced degree in Computer Science, IT, Mathematics, or related field
• Excellent organizational and time management skills

Preferred Qualifications:
• Located near or within driving distance of Springfield, IL
• 5+ years of data warehouse development experience
• 5+ years of data modeling using ERWIN or similar tools
• 2+ years of experience with Azure Data Factory and Snowflake
• Familiarity with scripting languages like Python, R, or JavaScript/React
• Experience with Informatica Data Quality (IDQ), Address Doctor, or Metadata Manager
• Experience working in Agile environments
• Exposure to Medicaid, Medicare, or healthcare data systems and standards

Location & Travel

This is a telecommute role with occasional travel (<15%) to Springfield, IL for client meetings.

At CSpring, we unlock the potential in people and data. If you’re a hands-on technologist who thrives in a fast-moving, impact-driven environment, we’d love to connect. Apply today to help shape the future of healthcare data infrastructure.

description:
Company Description

The Weather Channel is the world's leading cross-platform media company with a portfolio that includes The Weather Channel television network, TWC digital properties (weather.com, mobile and tablet applications) and Weather Services International (WSI). Headquartered in Cobb County since 1982, The Weather Channel brand has connected millions of consumers by providing the most accurate weather forecasts, 24 hours a day. Seen in more than 100 million U.S. households, The Weather Channel network is one of the most widely-distributed cable networks. The Weather Channel online properties reach 60 million unique Web consumers each month. This includes 32 million consumers monthly through weather.com on mobile Web and mobile apps. TWC has the No.1 app on all smartphones and is the second most used app on all smartphones. WSI provides business-to-business weather services to media, aviation, marine and energy sectors.

Job Description

The ETL Informatica Systems Engineer will support of our EDW/BI program. This individual will act as the Sr. ETL Engineer for the TWC EDW/BI project and will be responsible for developing ETL applications using Informatica. Successful candidates will have demonstrated proficiency using the Informatica Suite of tools including Standard Edition Power Center, Team Based Development, Parallel Processing, and more. The role will focus on developing Extract, Transformation and Loading (ETL) procedures for implementing data integration and data loading tasks in support of the EDW/BI project.

Qualifications

·BS in computer science, or its equivalent

·7 years of relevant experience with demonstrated proficiency and progressive responsibilities to include the following experiences:

·Informatica PowerCenter

·Linux

·Solid MS SQL Server database skills including the ability to write complex SQL and stored procedures

·Fact and Dimensional data, including slowly changing dimensions

·Demonstrated proficiency with SOAP/XML and REST/JSON API use, including the use of oAuth and oAuth2.

·Demonstrated ability to establish priorities, organize and plan work to satisfy established timeframes.

·Proven ability to handle multiple tasks and projects simultaneously.

·Demonstrated experience in performance tuning for Informatica ETL processing

·Excellent analytical skills, attention to detail and problem-solving skills.

·Demonstrated proficiency converting shell and Perl programming to Informatica Objects

·Strong interpersonal and leadership skills and demonstrated ability to work comfortably with all levels within an organization and across business function

·Demonstrated proficiency with any of the following will be considered a plus.

·Contract Management Systems (Operative.one),

·Ad Delivery Systems (Google Double Click for Publishers Premium),

·Omniture,

·Nielson Ratings data,

·Peoplesoft Financials,

·Salesforce

·Yieldex

·Java and Perl programming

Additional Information

Must apply to: https://career8.successfactors.com/sfcareer/jobreqcareer?jobId=1475&company=3323768P&username=

Requisition Number: 1475

description:
Journey with us! Combine your career goals and sense of adventure by joining our exciting team of employees. Royal Caribbean Group is pleased to offer a competitive compensation and benefits package, and excellent career development opportunities, each offering unique ways to explore the world.

The Royal Caribbean Group’s Data Analytics and AI Team has an exciting career opportunity for a full time Senior Engineer, Informatica MDM reporting to the Director of Enterprise MDM & Quality.

This position will work on-site in Miramar, Florida.

Position Summary

We are seeking an experienced MDM Developer with a strong focus on Informatica SAS MDM and Party Model implementation. The ideal candidate will be responsible for configuring and customizing the MDM platform, ensuring data accuracy and consistency, integrating data from various sources, and optimizing performance. Proficiency in data quality management, data modeling, and effective communication with cross-functional teams is essential for this role.

Essential Duties and Responsibilities
• Informatica SAS MDM Configuration: Configure and customize Informatica SAS MDM to implement the Party Model, defining entity types, relationships, business rules, match and merge strategies, and user interfaces.
• Data Modelling: Work with data architects and stakeholders to design and maintain the data model for party-related entities within the Informatica SAS MDM platform, ensuring data accuracy and consistency.
• Data Integration: Integrate data from various source systems into Informatica’s SAS MDM platform through IDMC, performing data profiling, cleansing, and transformation to ensure data quality and integrity.
• Match and Merge: Implement match and merge rules to identify and consolidate duplicate records within the party entities, enabling a single and accurate view of each entity.
• Configure Address Doctor Engine-reference and email and phone verification.
• Data Quality Management: Define and implement data quality rules and workflows within the SAS MDM system to monitor, measure, and improve data quality across party related data.
• Experieince working with Refernce 360 and it’s usage within the MDM domain.
• Performance Optimization: Identify performance bottlenecks within the SAS MDM system and optimize data loading, matching, and retrieval processes for efficient and seamless data operations.
• Testing and Validation: Conduct unit testing and integration testing to validate MDM configurations, ensuring accuracy and completeness of data within the MDM repository.
• Documentation: Maintain comprehensive technical documentation, including design specifications, configuration guides, and troubleshooting manuals for the MDM implementation.
• Build UNIX shell scripting, Pre-Session, Post-Session UNIX Commands for automation of Informatica job scheduling, backup of repository etc.
• Work with SFTP/SSH file transfer and loading using SQL, PL/SQL, SQL *Loader.

Position Requirements
• Bachelor's Degree from an accredited college or university with a major in Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering, Business, or other related scientific or technical discipline.
• 4+ years of experience in MDM Development experience with a focus on Informatica MDM and Party Model implementation.
• Must have hands on experience implementing Informatica’s SAS MDM application.
• Experieince working with Refernce 360 and it’s usage within the MDM domain.
• Experience working with CAI, CDI and CDQ is a must.
• In-depth knowledge of Informatica’s SAS MDM tools, including IDMC, and their functionalities for party entities.
• Familiarity with data modelling principles and data integration techniques.
• Strong understanding of data quality management and data governance practices within an MDM environment.
• Proficiency in data profiling, data cleansing, and data transformation processes.
• Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills to troubleshoot MDM-related issues.
• Strong communication and collaboration skills to work effectively with cross functional teams and stakeholders.
• Knowledgeable in technology and software development processes.
• Good presentation development and delivery skills.
• Fair understanding of Agile methodologies (e.g., Scrum, Kanban) required.
• Experience with travel and hospitality industry is a huge plus.
• Knowledge of Data Warehouses/Lakehouse architectures, Master Data Management, Data Quality Management, Data Integration, and Data Warehouse architecture.

We know there's a lot to consider. As you go through the application process, our recruiters will be glad to provide guidance, and more relevant details to answer any additional questions. Thank you again for your interest in Royal Caribbean Group. We'll hope to see you onboard soon!

It is the policy of the Company to ensure equal employment and promotion opportunity to qualified candidates without discrimination or harassment on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, age, national origin, disability, sexual orientation, sexuality, gender identity or expression, marital status, or any other characteristic protected by law. Royal Caribbean Group and each of its subsidiaries prohibit and will not tolerate discrimination or harassment.

description:
Senior Informatica/ETL Developer with master’s degree in Computer Science/Applications, Engineering (any), Technology or related and 2 yrs. of exp to Work on Informatica Power Center tools- Designer, Repository Manager, Workflow Manager, and Workflow Monitor. Responsible for creating Functional design specifications and mapping documents for end-to-end ETL process flow. Design and develop ETL code that meets technical specifications and business requirements according to the established designs and framework. Provide production support for ETL batch and real time process. Develop Mappings, Workflows, reusable and non-reusable session tasks. Use various transformations like Filter, Expression, Sequence Generator, Update Strategy, Joiner, Stored Procedure, and Union to develop robust mappings in the Informatica Designer.

Work location is Allen, TX with required travel to client locations throughout the USA. Please mail resumes to e-mail: hr@sentiertech.com

description:
Minimum Mandatory Skills:
• 7+ years of experience in Informatica PowerCenter development and ETL processes.
• Strong knowledge of SQL and relational databases such as Oracle, SQL Server, MySQL, or DB2.
Desired Skills
• Experience with data warehousing concepts, dimensional modeling, and data marts.
• Proficiency in performance tuning and optimization of complex ETL jobs.
• Hands-on experience with cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, Azure, Google Cloud) is a plus.
• Strong analytical, problem-solving, and debugging skills.
• Excellent communication and team collaboration abilities.
Job Description
We are seeking a highly skilled Informatica Lead Developer to manage our data integration efforts, focusing on the design, development, and implementation of ETL solutions. The ideal candidate will have extensive experience with Informatica PowerCenter, cloud platforms, and a deep understanding of data warehousing concepts.

Key Responsibilities:
• Lead the design, development, and implementation of ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) processes using Informatica PowerCenter or other Informatica tools.
• Collaborate with business analysts, data architects, and stakeholders to gather requirements and design ETL workflows.
• Optimize and tune existing Informatica processes to improve performance and scalability.
• Lead and mentor junior developers, ensuring best practices and coding standards are followed.
• Develop and maintain technical documentation for ETL processes, data flow, and error handling.
• Troubleshoot data integration and transformation issues and provide root cause analysis.
• Collaborate with the Data Warehouse team to integrate new data sources and ensure consistency in data flows.
• Manage and schedule ETL jobs, ensuring successful data load, transformation, and migration activities.
• Work closely with the database administrators and other IT teams to ensure seamless data delivery.
• Support production ETL processes and resolve any data discrepancies or job failures.

description:
Senior Informatica Administrator

We are seeking an experienced and proficient Senior Informatica Administrator with over 7 years of expertise to join our dynamic IT team. As a key member responsible for managing our Informatica platform, you will play a crucial role in overseeing the installation, configuration, and optimization of Informatica environments. Your extensive experience in Informatica administration will be essential in ensuring the reliability, performance, and security of our data integration and ETL processes.

Responsibilities:
• Installation and Configuration: Lead the installation and configuration of Informatica PowerCenter and related components, ensuring optimal performance and scalability.
• Environment Management: Manage and maintain multiple Informatica environments, including development, testing, and production, to support the full software development lifecycle.
• Performance Tuning: Implement performance tuning strategies to optimize Informatica workflows, mappings, and sessions for efficient ETL processing.
• Security Management: Establish and enforce security policies and access controls within the Informatica environment, ensuring data integrity and compliance with organizational standards.
• Monitoring and Troubleshooting: Monitor system performance, troubleshoot issues, and implement corrective actions to minimize downtime and enhance system reliability.
• Backup and Recovery: Implement and manage backup and recovery strategies to safeguard Informatica metadata and configurations, ensuring data integrity in case of system failures.
• Patch and Upgrade Management: Plan and execute Informatica software upgrades and apply patches to stay current with the latest features, security updates, and bug fixes.
• Metadata Management: Oversee metadata management, ensuring consistency and accuracy of metadata across different environments.
• Collaboration: Collaborate with development teams, database administrators, and other stakeholders to support data integration requirements and resolve dependencies.
• Documentation: Maintain comprehensive documentation of Informatica configurations, processes, and procedures.

Requirements:
• Bachelor//'s or Master//'s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field.
• Over 7 years of proven experience as an Informatica Administrator in a large-scale enterprise environment.
• Expertise in installing, configuring, and administering Informatica PowerCenter, PowerExchange, and related tools.
• Strong understanding of ETL concepts, data integration, and data warehousing.
• Experience in performance tuning and optimizing Informatica workflows for large datasets.
• Knowledge of security best practices for Informatica environments, including user access management and encryption.
• Proficiency in monitoring tools for Informatica and experience in proactive issue identification and resolution.
• Experience with Informatica upgrades, patches, and applying hotfixes.
• Strong SQL and relational database skills.
• Excellent communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively in a team environment.

description:
Informatica/ETL Developer
Location : New York city (Remote to start)
Type : 06 months
Rate : DOE
Start date : Immediately

US citizen, Green card H4 EAD and GC EAD accepted & will be remote until the virus subsides.

Required
• Development on Informatica tools: Informatica Power Center, Informatica Cloud and other tools.
• Develop ETL workflows using Informatica for data loads from source to target databases.
• Determine appropriate translations between source and target, capture metadata, load and transform data from data sources into target.
• Design and implement appropriate error handling procedures.
• Monitor performance, troubleshoot and tune ETL processes.
• Work closely with the architect and engineers to design systems effectively reflect business needs, security requirements and service level requirements.
• Research and investigate any Informatica issues. Develop a deep understanding of the relationship between various business process, systems, and the underlying data.
• Create mapping /requirement document, ETL design documents, Unit Test cases, code repository and other relevant documents. Coordinate with application team and develop all ETL processes.

job_title: Informatica Developer with Strong SQL / Remote (Denver, CO ), 3+ Months Contract
description:
Remote Role, Location is no preference ,10+ years of experienced candidates only
Job Description

The contractor will need experience in Informatica and SQL. This involves using Informatica and SQL to load tables and generate files for federal reporting. In addition, this individual may be requested to provide recommendations, documentation, and knowledge transfer to the CDE staff. With this partnership the need for knowledge transfer should happen in the normal course of work between the DW team and the contractor.
• Included in the daily work but not limited to, is maintaining the existing Oracle Data Warehouse environment and ETL development.
• The contractor will need experience in Informatica and SQL. This involves using Informatica and SQL to load tables and generate files for federal reporting. In addition, this individual may be requested to provide recommendations, documentation, and knowledge transfer to the CDE staff.
• With this partnership the need for knowledge transfer should happen in the normal course of work between the DW team and the contractor.
Balance SLDS Work With DAILY Maintenance of our existing structure
• With the guidance of the data warehouse manager and in partnership with a DW employee, the contractor shall
• Review internal CDE documentation and provide maintenance and support for the existing CDE Informatica and SQL processes.
• Review status on the SLDS project and perform tasks as determined by the partnership. This may include, but is not limited to, mapping of data fields to the new environment and structures, migrating data, testing, and other duties as assigned in the MS Azure cloud environment using SQL and possibly Data Factory skills
Informatica Skills
• Strong development skills: ability to develop very difficult or complicated transformation from scratch
• Strong administrative skills including repository management and knowledge of best practices regarding Informatica
• Strong oral and written communication skills working with both business users and technical staff
• The contractor shall demonstrate their understanding of the overall project goals and the specific goals as pertains to the contractor's assignment for this project to the satisfaction of the Project Manager.
• The contractor be able to advise and provide guidance on the requested work.
• The contractor shall develop, maintain, and support Extract Transform and Load processes which are written using Informatica and SQL.
• The contractor shall use Informatica and SQL to load the CDE Data Warehouse tables and generate Ed Facts files for federal reporting.
• The contractor shall thoroughly test and document each step taken and perform knowledge transfer to the CDE staff.
Others
• Contractor shall provide its their own computer hardware and software necessary to perform the Work at CDE's facilities.
• If working at the CDE office, CDE will provide the contractor with office space, phone, and internet access at CDE's Colfax office subject to all applicable health and safety guidelines and requirements.
• While working remotely at locations other than CDE's office, CDE will provide the contractor with virtual access to the data and systems necessary for completion of the Work.
• The Contractor shall provide documentation to the Project Manager. This documentation must provide details on the work provided and at a level a Department employee can use the information to support the work at the end of the contract.
• The Contractor shall submit detailed status reports or participate in weekly status meetings as required by the Department during the engagement.
• The Contractor shall attend required meetings with the required project stakeholders as directed by the Department. These meetings will be scheduled by a Department employee. All questions and communication should go through the Project Manager, Kevin Smith. If Kevin is not available, he will designate a Department employee for the communication.
• Contractor shall retain all work papers generated for reference through the duration of the project and project acceptance.
• Contractor shall respond to all telephone calls, voicemail, and e-mail inquiries from the Department within one business day.
